This paper deals with channel equalization and decoding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses variational autoencoders (VAEs), which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for the equalization process, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). The paper also deals with signal processing (cs.SI) and communication theory (cs.CL), which are related sub-fields.
